1
00:00:01,876 --> 00:00:06,214
[thrilling music playing]

2
00:00:06,297 --> 00:00:13,304
[crowd cheering]

3
00:00:14,597 --> 00:00:19,436
[crowd chanting]
<i>BINI, BINI, BINI, BINI, BINI!</i>

4
00:00:19,519 --> 00:00:25,817
- ["Pantropiko" playing]
- [crowd cheering]

5
00:00:27,902 --> 00:00:30,613
[reporter 1] <i>BINI fever is so on!</i>

6
00:00:30,697 --> 00:00:32,407
<i>As soon as BINI came out,</i>

7
00:00:32,490 --> 00:00:35,702
<i>the crowd went wild
inside the event venue.</i>

8
00:00:35,785 --> 00:00:37,495
[crowd chanting] <i>BINI, BINI, BINI!</i>

9
00:00:37,579 --> 00:00:40,707
[reporter 2] <i>The audience
screamed and jammed the arena</i>

10
00:00:40,790 --> 00:00:43,334
<i>to find their spot and watch the group.</i>

11
00:00:43,418 --> 00:00:45,503
[Stacey] <i>Is this for real,
or are they ghosts?</i>

12
00:00:45,587 --> 00:00:47,297
<i>Because this is unbelievable!</i>

13
00:00:47,380 --> 00:00:49,132
<i>Our Blooms grew rapidly!</i>

14
00:00:49,215 --> 00:00:50,717
[reporter 3] <i>BINI has secured</i>

15
00:00:50,800 --> 00:00:55,055
<i>the No. 1 spot on Spotify
Daily Top Artists Philippines.</i>

16
00:00:55,138 --> 00:00:58,892
<i>BINI has once again entered
the GlobalTop Artists Chart</i>

17
00:00:58,975 --> 00:01:00,977
<i>of the said music streaming platform.</i>

18
00:01:01,061 --> 00:01:04,898
[reporter 4] <i>The Blooms filled the streets
outside of ABS-CBN.</i>

19
00:01:04,981 --> 00:01:06,524
[Sheena] <i>It's super unexpected.</i>

20
00:01:06,608 --> 00:01:08,777
<i>It's like anything can happen overnight.</i>

21
00:01:08,860 --> 00:01:11,196
<i>Blooms! Blooms!</i>

22
00:01:11,279 --> 00:01:13,490
<i>They're so</i> [bleep] <i>popular there.</i>

23
00:01:13,573 --> 00:01:14,657
<i>Rightfully so.</i>

24
00:01:18,411 --> 00:01:20,705
<i>I love these girls so much.
Wow.</i>

25
00:01:20,789 --> 00:01:24,209
<i>This is pure bliss. These girls are...</i>

26
00:01:24,793 --> 00:01:25,835
<i>Yes.</i>

27
00:01:25,919 --> 00:01:28,963
[Gwen] <i>We are super blessed
with all the projects</i>

28
00:01:29,047 --> 00:01:31,216
<i>that, back then, we could only pray for.</i>

29
00:01:31,299 --> 00:01:34,385
<i>But at the same time, it's overwhelming.</i>

30
00:01:34,469 --> 00:01:38,473
<i>We have many internal struggles
that not everyone knows about.</i>

31
00:01:38,556 --> 00:01:42,894
[Sheena] <i>It really taught us
to support one another.</i>

32
00:01:42,977 --> 00:01:45,355
<i>We have each other's backs.</i>

33
00:01:46,981 --> 00:01:51,319
[thrilling music playing]

34
00:01:51,402 --> 00:01:52,904
<i>- Rolling?
- Cameras rolling.</i>

35
00:01:52,987 --> 00:01:55,448
<i>- Rolling?
- Rolling.</i>

36
00:01:55,532 --> 00:01:57,951
Hi! This is BINI Jhoanna.

37
00:01:58,034 --> 00:02:00,411
Hi, I'm BINI Sheena.

38
00:02:01,204 --> 00:02:03,998
I'm BINI. Let's go. Let's do this.

39
00:02:04,082 --> 00:02:06,584
Hi, guys! I'm BINI Gwen.

40
00:02:06,668 --> 00:02:08,503
Hi! I'm Colet.

41
00:02:08,586 --> 00:02:10,130
Hi, everyone.

42
00:02:10,213 --> 00:02:14,092
Hi, Blooms and the whole entire world.

43
00:02:14,175 --> 00:02:16,719
I'm Maloi from BINI. Hello.

44
00:02:16,803 --> 00:02:20,140
Hi, everyone! I'm Mikha Lim from BINI.

45
00:02:20,223 --> 00:02:23,101
Hi, I'm Aiah, the eldest of the group.

46
00:02:23,184 --> 00:02:25,812
Hi! I'm BINI Stacey.

47
00:02:25,895 --> 00:02:28,022
Welcome to Chapter... Chapter?

48
00:02:28,106 --> 00:02:29,357
Welcome to Chapter Two!

49
00:02:30,692 --> 00:02:31,943
Good morning!

50
00:02:40,285 --> 00:02:43,121
[reporter 5] <i>BINI's three-night concert
was a huge success!</i>

51
00:02:43,204 --> 00:02:47,792
<i>The Blooms greatly enjoyed
the three-hour concert.</i>

52
00:02:50,003 --> 00:02:54,507
<i>They are taking the show
to Baguio, Cebu, and General Santos City.</i>

53
00:03:02,307 --> 00:03:03,391
[Sheena singing] ♪<i>...going on a trip ♪</i>

54
00:03:03,474 --> 00:03:05,018
<i>♪ In our favorite rocket ship ♪</i>

55
00:03:05,101 --> 00:03:07,604
<i>♪ Going through the moon ♪</i>

56
00:03:07,687 --> 00:03:09,397
<i>♪ Little Sheena ♪</i>

57
00:03:10,106 --> 00:03:12,609
<i>♪ Ride aboard Get ready to explore ♪</i>

58
00:03:12,692 --> 00:03:17,071
<i>♪ Going to the sun In the sun rays ♪</i>

59
00:03:17,697 --> 00:03:19,407
Guys, the view here is so nice.

60
00:03:19,490 --> 00:03:24,412
But I can't stay here alone at night
because there are so many trees.

61
00:03:24,495 --> 00:03:27,874
Imagine, I'm walking and
someone suddenly grabs me!

62
00:03:29,083 --> 00:03:31,878
An ogre. It's actually Jho's family.

63
00:03:32,795 --> 00:03:33,922
Jho.

64
00:03:34,464 --> 00:03:36,633
What time do you guys
usually come out here?

65
00:03:36,716 --> 00:03:38,509
Midnight to 3AM. Around that time.

66
00:03:38,593 --> 00:03:40,637
Midnight to 3AM?

67
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:42,305
Shucks! No, it's fine.

68
00:03:42,388 --> 00:03:45,266
[Jhoanna] We like to enjoy
the surroundings.

69
00:03:45,350 --> 00:03:46,351
[laughs]

70
00:03:46,434 --> 00:03:47,894
What's happening?

71
00:03:47,977 --> 00:03:52,982
You see, ogres come out here
at midnight to 1AM.

72
00:03:53,608 --> 00:03:55,109
So I told Jho--

73
00:03:55,193 --> 00:03:58,404
Oh, look! A couple! There's a couple!

74
00:03:58,988 --> 00:04:01,115
You get distracted so easily.

75
00:04:01,199 --> 00:04:02,116
[laughs]

76
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:04,911
They exchanged gifts
in the middle of the road.

77
00:04:04,994 --> 00:04:06,329
I can't even!

78
00:04:06,412 --> 00:04:08,289
Guys, fun fact.

79
00:04:08,373 --> 00:04:10,917
Actually, it's not a fun fact.
It's a sad fact.

80
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:15,713
Gwen and Maloi have their own rooms
because they're feeling under the weather.

81
00:04:15,797 --> 00:04:17,715
They are literally under the weather.

82
00:04:17,799 --> 00:04:19,092
They're feeling under the weather--

83
00:04:19,175 --> 00:04:21,219
Oh no! Now I'm in the dark.

84
00:04:21,302 --> 00:04:22,303
There.

85
00:04:22,804 --> 00:04:24,389
They're feeling under the-- Oh!

86
00:04:24,973 --> 00:04:26,766
The camera keeps blacking out.

87
00:04:26,849 --> 00:04:28,476
Let's start with the first one.

88
00:04:28,559 --> 00:04:29,477
Baguio.

89
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:35,566
The last time we went to Baguio,
we weren't that popular yet.

90
00:04:35,650 --> 00:04:38,111
[rapping] <i>We are here On Session Road</i>

91
00:04:38,194 --> 00:04:40,655
[beating drums]

92
00:04:40,738 --> 00:04:41,656
[clapping]

93
00:04:41,739 --> 00:04:42,782
[laughing]

94
00:04:42,865 --> 00:04:45,493
We get nervous during regional gigs

95
00:04:45,576 --> 00:04:48,246
because we don't know
if people will show up.

96
00:04:48,329 --> 00:04:51,708
My mindset is to just have fun.

97
00:04:51,791 --> 00:04:53,459
We get exposed to different personalities,

98
00:04:53,543 --> 00:04:56,546
different experiences,
and different cultures

99
00:04:56,629 --> 00:04:59,799
in different parts of the Philippines.

100
00:04:59,882 --> 00:05:06,597
[performing "Na Na Na"]

101
00:05:10,476 --> 00:05:17,483
["Na Na Na" playing]

102
00:05:24,198 --> 00:05:28,661
This is my first time seeing the hall.

103
00:05:28,745 --> 00:05:32,874
I'm excited to see
the Baguio Blooms later!

104
00:05:34,792 --> 00:05:38,796
[Gwen] <i>They've been here
since before 10AM.</i>

105
00:05:39,422 --> 00:05:40,298
What time is the show?

106
00:05:40,381 --> 00:05:42,717
- They'll let people in at 5PM.
- 7PM. I see.

107
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:44,510
Maybe they're just hanging around.

108
00:05:44,594 --> 00:05:45,928
[Gwen] But still, right?

109
00:05:46,012 --> 00:05:49,223
Also, check out that open area over there.

110
00:05:49,307 --> 00:05:50,391
True!

111
00:05:50,475 --> 00:05:52,143
Those are the real Blooms.

112
00:05:52,226 --> 00:05:53,603
I hope it never ends.

113
00:05:53,686 --> 00:05:55,438
Oh, yes! I hope this lasts.

114
00:05:55,521 --> 00:05:56,939
We'll get used to it eventually.

115
00:05:57,857 --> 00:06:00,109
Actually, I prefer it this way.

116
00:06:00,193 --> 00:06:01,694
I like being busy.

117
00:06:01,778 --> 00:06:03,321
It's scarier when you're doing nothing.

118
00:06:03,404 --> 00:06:04,989
That's true.

119
00:06:05,406 --> 00:06:07,116
- We're happy this way.
- Just keep us busy, Lord.

120
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:08,117
Thank you, Lord, for the blessings.

121
00:06:08,201 --> 00:06:10,203
Just give us all
the blessings in the world.

122
00:06:10,870 --> 00:06:15,708
[gentle music playing]

123
00:06:15,792 --> 00:06:17,502
Hi!

124
00:06:17,585 --> 00:06:19,921
Hi, everyone. Hi, Blooms.

125
00:06:20,004 --> 00:06:22,965
So, welcome to my room.

126
00:06:23,049 --> 00:06:27,720
So, Blooms, after our three-day concert,

127
00:06:27,804 --> 00:06:32,225
we were able to have
our three-day... [chuckles]

128
00:06:32,308 --> 00:06:35,353
Three days of rest.

129
00:06:35,436 --> 00:06:40,399
My parents picked me up
from my place on the second day,

130
00:06:40,483 --> 00:06:44,112
and then we went to Batangas.

131
00:06:44,195 --> 00:06:47,281
It made me happy because it's my hometown.

132
00:06:48,783 --> 00:06:50,493
[Maloi] <i>I grew up in Batangas,</i>

133
00:06:50,576 --> 00:06:53,871
<i>but we lived in Palawan
for a couple of years.</i>

134
00:06:53,955 --> 00:06:57,291
Then we moved back to Batangas

135
00:06:57,375 --> 00:06:59,293
and eventually settled in Cavite.

136
00:06:59,377 --> 00:07:02,296
So I never stayed in one school
for more than three years.

137
00:07:02,380 --> 00:07:05,716
I think that experience
taught me how to be sociable.

138
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:08,469
It's why I easily get along with people.

139
00:07:08,553 --> 00:07:11,013
I'm a real Batangueña.

140
00:07:11,097 --> 00:07:13,141
A real Batangueña.

141
00:07:13,224 --> 00:07:15,143
She's really the clown of the family.

142
00:07:15,226 --> 00:07:18,729
We can't stop laughing
every time she does impressions.

143
00:07:18,813 --> 00:07:21,107
[in a Batangas accent]
Eros, where did you go?

144
00:07:21,607 --> 00:07:22,608
Where?

145
00:07:23,109 --> 00:07:24,152
Where is that?

146
00:07:24,235 --> 00:07:27,196
Whenever I meet someone from Batangas,

147
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:34,078
the Batangueña in me
just comes out naturally.

148
00:07:34,412 --> 00:07:37,999
When we're all together,
we always have a great time.

149
00:07:38,082 --> 00:07:40,626
She doesn't take things too seriously.

150
00:07:40,710 --> 00:07:42,628
She makes everyone laugh.

151
00:07:43,296 --> 00:07:48,926
So when she's not around,
things become quiet.

152
00:07:49,010 --> 00:07:50,845
We feel like something is missing.

153
00:07:50,928 --> 00:07:53,222
Actually, we weren't used
to being a complete family.

154
00:07:53,306 --> 00:07:56,809
[Maloi] <i>My dad left when I was young
to work abroad.</i>

155
00:07:57,351 --> 00:07:59,812
<i>He was gonefor 13 long years.</i>

156
00:07:59,896 --> 00:08:03,399
<i>He'd come home every year for Christmas,</i>

157
00:08:03,483 --> 00:08:07,195
<i>but it was hard to say goodbye every time.</i>

158
00:08:07,278 --> 00:08:10,198
We'd count down the days
until he came back.

159
00:08:10,281 --> 00:08:11,407
It was tough.

160
00:08:11,491 --> 00:08:12,617
[crowd cheering]

161
00:08:12,700 --> 00:08:16,329
[fan] Maloi! Maloi!

162
00:08:16,412 --> 00:08:18,623
I'm really overwhelmed
by what's happening.

163
00:08:18,706 --> 00:08:20,708
[Maggie] <i>I'd get teary-eyed.
I would just cry.</i>

164
00:08:20,791 --> 00:08:25,087
<i>I would thank the Lord
for answeringour prayers.</i>

165
00:08:25,171 --> 00:08:28,799
<i>Sometimes Maloi and I would argue.</i>

166
00:08:28,883 --> 00:08:31,928
One time she cried, "Mama, you
don't understand. I'm so tired!"

167
00:08:32,011 --> 00:08:37,099
She just cried her heart out
and then she felt better,

168
00:08:37,183 --> 00:08:39,560
and then I apologized. [chuckles]

169
00:08:39,644 --> 00:08:41,896
We miss her so much.
We barely spend time together.

170
00:08:41,979 --> 00:08:45,107
It's the price we pay
for her current success.

171
00:08:45,191 --> 00:08:46,776
[Mikha] First time!

172
00:08:46,859 --> 00:08:50,488
[upbeat music playing]

173
00:08:50,571 --> 00:08:51,572
Censored!

174
00:08:51,656 --> 00:08:53,908
Because it's gross,
they're going to blur it.

175
00:08:53,991 --> 00:08:54,951
[chuckles]

176
00:08:55,034 --> 00:09:00,540
[upbeat music continues]

177
00:09:00,623 --> 00:09:01,624
Go, sir!

178
00:09:04,085 --> 00:09:07,255
[coach] Girls, if it's okay with you,
let's all do a soundcheck.

179
00:09:07,338 --> 00:09:12,426
[upbeat music continues]

180
00:09:12,510 --> 00:09:15,429
[coach] Let's do the blocking,
then we'll take a video.

181
00:09:15,972 --> 00:09:16,889
So five, six...

182
00:09:17,557 --> 00:09:19,934
So what's going to happen...

183
00:09:20,017 --> 00:09:22,603
[Mickey] <i>What's also different
here is the Pantropiko.</i>

184
00:09:22,687 --> 00:09:25,022
<i>So we were thinking
ofhow we can give them</i>

185
00:09:25,106 --> 00:09:27,400
<i>a different impact
and a different experience.</i>

186
00:09:27,483 --> 00:09:29,819
And I think one of the best experiences

187
00:09:29,902 --> 00:09:33,197
for a Bloom or for anyone
is having them close by.

188
00:09:33,281 --> 00:09:35,825
So what we did in <i>Pantropiko</i> is,

189
00:09:35,908 --> 00:09:38,953
if the crowd is game and they're okay,

190
00:09:39,036 --> 00:09:42,623
we're going to have them
go down in the fan interaction.

191
00:09:42,707 --> 00:09:49,505
["Espresso" by Sabrina Carpenter playing]

192
00:09:49,589 --> 00:09:51,090
[cameraman] How was your sleep?

193
00:09:51,799 --> 00:09:53,384
Did you catch up on sleep?

194
00:09:54,176 --> 00:09:56,512
I don't know what happened.
I wasn't sleepy earlier.

195
00:09:56,596 --> 00:09:58,097
[cameraman] You were sleeping heavily!

196
00:09:58,180 --> 00:09:59,181
[chuckles]

197
00:10:00,891 --> 00:10:02,602
[Jhoanna] <i>When I was a kid,</i>

198
00:10:02,685 --> 00:10:05,563
<i>I used to talk to myself a lot
in front of the mirror.</i>

199
00:10:05,646 --> 00:10:07,189
I'd buy a box of chalk,

200
00:10:07,273 --> 00:10:10,026
then I'd write all over our wall
and pretend to be a teacher.

201
00:10:10,109 --> 00:10:14,196
My students were my pillows,
and I gave them names.

202
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:16,324
Or I'd play restaurant where I
was the cook and the customer.

203
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:22,622
[Jhonna] <i>She grew up an only child,
so you'd expect her to be spoiled.</i>

204
00:10:22,705 --> 00:10:24,999
But no. She's really independent.

205
00:10:25,082 --> 00:10:26,792
She can handle everything.

206
00:10:26,876 --> 00:10:27,793
She's tough.

207
00:10:27,877 --> 00:10:31,297
Maybe she got used to it
because she used to play alone.

208
00:10:32,256 --> 00:10:34,342
[Boyet] <i>She did everything alone.</i>

209
00:10:34,425 --> 00:10:37,011
[Jhoanna] <i>Dad worked as a seafarer abroad.</i>

210
00:10:37,511 --> 00:10:41,766
I vividly remember
that every time my dad left,

211
00:10:41,849 --> 00:10:43,392
I would cry my eyes out.

212
00:10:43,476 --> 00:10:45,478
Every single time.

213
00:10:45,561 --> 00:10:48,022
And when he'd come home
sporting long hair,

214
00:10:48,105 --> 00:10:50,775
<i>I would also cry
because it would scare me.</i>

215
00:10:50,858 --> 00:10:54,528
He said it was because haircuts
were pretty expensive on board.

216
00:10:54,612 --> 00:10:57,823
If he hadn't made the sacrifice
to work abroad as a seafarer,

217
00:10:57,907 --> 00:11:02,620
I don't think they could've afforded
to send me to a good school.

218
00:11:02,703 --> 00:11:08,209
Because even though I'm an only child,
we weren't that well-off

219
00:11:08,292 --> 00:11:11,003
for them to provide everything for me.

220
00:11:11,087 --> 00:11:14,048
[Jhonna] <i>Even now, it still feels unreal</i>

221
00:11:14,131 --> 00:11:18,886
that she's already made it,
that she's become a household name.

222
00:11:18,969 --> 00:11:22,473
Sometimes I can't help but ask
if all of this is real.

223
00:11:32,108 --> 00:11:34,610
[Boyet] You see? She's made me her driver.

224
00:11:34,693 --> 00:11:35,903
[Jhoanna chuckles]

225
00:11:35,986 --> 00:11:38,906
[Boyet] We couldn't stop her
because she really wanted it,

226
00:11:38,989 --> 00:11:42,618
so my wife and I
just chose to support her.

227
00:11:42,701 --> 00:11:49,041
There are times when she's
busy rehearsing or out-of-town.

228
00:11:49,125 --> 00:11:51,127
This must be how Daddy felt back then.

229
00:11:51,210 --> 00:11:54,505
It must've been worse for him
because he was on board a ship.

230
00:11:54,588 --> 00:11:58,008
He couldn't just leave if he wanted to.

231
00:11:58,092 --> 00:12:00,302
We adjust to her schedule.

232
00:12:00,386 --> 00:12:03,305
[Boyet] <i>We only go out
when she has free time.</i>

233
00:12:04,765 --> 00:12:11,397
[thrilling music playing]

234
00:12:18,737 --> 00:12:21,115
- One, two, three, BINIverse!
- One, two, three, BINIverse!

235
00:12:21,198 --> 00:12:24,118
- This is BINIverse!
- This is BINIverse!

236
00:12:24,201 --> 00:12:31,208
[Performing "Salamin, Salamin"]

237
00:12:38,007 --> 00:12:40,217
[crowd singing along]
<i>♪ I don't want to believe it ♪</i>

238
00:12:40,301 --> 00:12:42,011
[Speaking in Ilocano] <i>I can't believe...</i>

239
00:12:42,094 --> 00:12:45,389
- [crowd cheering]
- Was that right? Okay, one more!

240
00:12:47,183 --> 00:12:49,560
[Performing "Salamin, Salamin"]

241
00:12:49,643 --> 00:12:51,770
[crowd singing along]
<i>♪ I don't want to believe it ♪</i>

242
00:12:53,898 --> 00:12:55,858
I still can't believe it myself.

243
00:12:55,941 --> 00:12:59,528
To be honest, we weren't expecting things

244
00:12:59,612 --> 00:13:00,988
to blow up this fast.

245
00:13:01,071 --> 00:13:04,909
It's like BINI fever has taken over.

246
00:13:04,992 --> 00:13:06,327
It seems almost everyone knows

247
00:13:06,410 --> 00:13:08,787
who we are now and loves our songs.

248
00:13:08,871 --> 00:13:13,501
We've grown so much,
not just BINI but also the Blooms.

249
00:13:13,584 --> 00:13:20,299
[performing "Salamin, Salamin"]

250
00:13:24,386 --> 00:13:25,804
[Jhoanna] <i>My family came to watch.</i>

251
00:13:25,888 --> 00:13:27,723
<i>I think it's because of them
that I'm so strong now.</i>

252
00:13:27,806 --> 00:13:30,392
<i>I'm able to give so much love</i>

253
00:13:30,476 --> 00:13:35,898
<i>because they give me
so much love and support.</i>

254
00:13:39,026 --> 00:13:42,238
[tense music playing]

255
00:13:42,321 --> 00:13:44,573
There, go cool yourself!

256
00:13:47,576 --> 00:13:49,495
Plastic bag!

257
00:13:54,667 --> 00:13:57,211
We were all out of breath
just a few songs in.

258
00:13:57,294 --> 00:13:58,712
I couldn't sing well anymore.

259
00:13:58,796 --> 00:14:03,342
We kept asking for water backstage.

260
00:14:03,425 --> 00:14:04,385
It was stifling.

261
00:14:04,468 --> 00:14:09,181
I couldn't believe
it was so hot in Baguio.

262
00:14:09,265 --> 00:14:10,975
[crowd cheering]

263
00:14:11,058 --> 00:14:12,142
Oh my God!

264
00:14:12,226 --> 00:14:14,395
We felt so bad for the dancers.

265
00:14:14,478 --> 00:14:16,146
We were so worried.
We were like, "Just take a break

266
00:14:16,230 --> 00:14:18,732
Don't perform anymore. Stop."

267
00:14:18,816 --> 00:14:20,693
[Sheena] <i>Our dancer, JC, was throwing up.</i>

268
00:14:20,776 --> 00:14:24,405
I felt so bad for him.
It was heartbreaking.

269
00:14:24,488 --> 00:14:26,198
<i>And every time we went backstage,</i>

270
00:14:26,282 --> 00:14:29,827
<i>I'd see the dancers gasping for air.</i>

271
00:14:29,910 --> 00:14:32,121
We'd fan them and give them water

272
00:14:32,204 --> 00:14:35,708
<i>while we waited for our turn.</i>

273
00:14:36,292 --> 00:14:39,336
We really value our dancers.
They're part of the show.

274
00:14:39,420 --> 00:14:42,256
Without them, it won't be possible.

275
00:14:45,801 --> 00:14:52,099
[Sheena] <i>I'm a small-town girl
from Santiago City, Isabela.</i>

276
00:14:54,476 --> 00:14:57,813
<i>It was a pretty normal childhood.</i>

277
00:14:57,897 --> 00:15:00,691
<i>My mom was always encouraging me
to try new things,</i>

278
00:15:00,774 --> 00:15:02,610
<i>like joining workshops.</i>

279
00:15:02,693 --> 00:15:04,528
Yeah, my mom was my biggest fan.

280
00:15:04,612 --> 00:15:07,197
I feel like if she wasn't my mom,

281
00:15:07,281 --> 00:15:08,407
I wouldn't be where I am today.

282
00:15:08,490 --> 00:15:13,871
I'm pretty introverted,
so I need someone to push me.

283
00:15:13,954 --> 00:15:16,707
She was always that person for me.

284
00:15:16,790 --> 00:15:18,876
[staff] How did she push you?

285
00:15:18,959 --> 00:15:20,210
Like this. Just kidding. [chuckling]

286
00:15:20,294 --> 00:15:23,213
- She always motivated me.
- Good thing you didn't fall.

287
00:15:23,297 --> 00:15:25,507
[soft music playing]

288
00:15:25,591 --> 00:15:29,637
[Edita] <i>She never brings it up
because she doesn't want me to feel lonely</i>

289
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:32,514
when we talk about it.

290
00:15:32,598 --> 00:15:33,891
<i>She knows that I struggle with it.</i>

291
00:15:33,974 --> 00:15:35,559
<i>Instead of me comforting her,</i>

292
00:15:35,643 --> 00:15:39,521
she comforts me because she
doesn't have her mom anymore.

293
00:15:39,605 --> 00:15:41,899
<i>She's so protective of me.</i>

294
00:15:41,982 --> 00:15:43,525
Whenever she asks you to do something,

295
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:45,277
it's not an option not to go with it.

296
00:15:45,361 --> 00:15:48,614
<i>When she's home, she'd say,
"Let's make a TikTok, Grandma!"</i>

297
00:15:48,697 --> 00:15:52,201
It makes her happy that
we're somehow complete

298
00:15:52,284 --> 00:15:54,203
even without her mom around.

299
00:15:54,286 --> 00:15:56,455
<i>She's always there to console me.</i>

300
00:15:56,538 --> 00:16:00,459
I told her, "I see a lot
of your mom in you."

301
00:16:02,211 --> 00:16:03,712
[Sheena] I always say it must be destiny.

302
00:16:03,796 --> 00:16:06,423
This is really what God
had planned for me.

303
00:16:06,507 --> 00:16:08,217
So, I tell myself, "Go for it!
Keep on pushing!

304
00:16:08,300 --> 00:16:11,011
Turn whatever you're feeling
into inspiration.

305
00:16:11,095 --> 00:16:15,015
Go all out so you can be heard
all the way up in heaven."

306
00:16:15,099 --> 00:16:15,933
[chuckles]

307
00:16:16,016 --> 00:16:21,397
[Edita] I always tell her
to never forget her family,

308
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:23,524
especially God.

309
00:16:23,607 --> 00:16:26,610
And to pray always.

310
00:16:26,694 --> 00:16:28,779
Since we're far apart,

311
00:16:28,862 --> 00:16:31,657
I pray to God to keep her safe from harm.

312
00:16:31,740 --> 00:16:35,452
She told me that
if something happened to me,

313
00:16:35,536 --> 00:16:37,204
she wouldn't be able to handle it.

314
00:16:37,287 --> 00:16:38,789
I feel the same way.

315
00:16:38,872 --> 00:16:41,125
They're all I have left.

316
00:16:41,208 --> 00:16:44,128
I am old, and they are
my reason for staying on.

317
00:16:44,211 --> 00:16:47,756
So, I tell her to
take care of herself for me.

318
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:54,596
- [performing "Pantropiko"]
- [crowd cheering]

319
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:56,557
[Gwen] It was the first time
we went down to the crowd.

320
00:16:56,640 --> 00:16:59,601
We were so excited for the Blooms!

321
00:16:59,685 --> 00:17:03,439
We knew for sure they'd
have a blast, and they did!

322
00:17:03,522 --> 00:17:05,524
You don't see artists coming
down from the stage

323
00:17:05,607 --> 00:17:07,401
during a concert very often.

324
00:17:07,484 --> 00:17:11,447
I mean, if Twice did that,
I'd lose it! Can you imagine?

325
00:17:11,530 --> 00:17:14,199
[crowd cheering]

326
00:17:14,283 --> 00:17:20,706
- [Performing "Pantropiko"]
- [crowd singing along]

327
00:17:20,789 --> 00:17:23,834
[Aiah] At our concerts, I feel safe

328
00:17:23,917 --> 00:17:26,295
because they're all Blooms.

329
00:17:26,378 --> 00:17:28,213
It's like you're in a room
that's filled with people

330
00:17:28,297 --> 00:17:29,923
who know about you,

331
00:17:30,007 --> 00:17:32,676
who know your music,
and who really care about you.

332
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:35,512
[performing "Pantropiko"]

333
00:17:35,596 --> 00:17:38,515
I thought marshals were all no-nonsense.

334
00:17:38,599 --> 00:17:40,017
<i>This was the first time
I saw them loosen up.</i>

335
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:42,728
I figured they'd just be
keeping an eye on us.

336
00:17:42,811 --> 00:17:44,396
<i>But they were actually dancing along!</i>

337
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:45,481
It was so cool to see!

338
00:17:45,564 --> 00:17:46,523
I had an absolute blast! [clapping]

339
00:17:46,607 --> 00:17:49,985
[Maloi] <i>It was so fun
meeting Blooms up close.</i>

340
00:17:50,069 --> 00:17:54,490
If only I could meet each
and every one of them, I would!

341
00:17:54,573 --> 00:17:58,827
- [performing "Pantropiko"]
- [crowd cheering]

342
00:17:58,911 --> 00:18:01,246
Yay! Baguio done!

343
00:18:01,330 --> 00:18:03,499
- [staff] Congrats!
- Thank you! Thank you!

344
00:18:05,542 --> 00:18:07,920
We're going to our hotel.

345
00:18:08,003 --> 00:18:10,714
We just ate here.

346
00:18:10,798 --> 00:18:12,216
We're returning to our room.

347
00:18:12,299 --> 00:18:15,052
But I am going out with my family!

348
00:18:15,135 --> 00:18:20,307
On the way back, we made a stop
at a roadside eatery

349
00:18:20,390 --> 00:18:21,600
<i>because we were starving.</i>

350
00:18:21,683 --> 00:18:25,145
<i>I was just scarfing down bulalo and fish.</i>

351
00:18:25,229 --> 00:18:27,314
<i>I was stuffing my mouth when some people
approached me for a photo.</i>

352
00:18:27,397 --> 00:18:28,482
<i>My uncle asked them</i>

353
00:18:28,565 --> 00:18:31,026
<i>if they could wait until I finished eating</i>

354
00:18:31,110 --> 00:18:33,737
<i>as my mouth was full.</i>

355
00:18:33,821 --> 00:18:35,697
They seemed kind of
disappointed and apologized,

356
00:18:35,781 --> 00:18:37,699
saying they had to head home.

357
00:18:37,783 --> 00:18:40,661
I just said, "Oh, okay."

358
00:18:40,744 --> 00:18:42,704
My pet peeve is being
interrupted while eating.

359
00:18:42,788 --> 00:18:44,123
That's just all I ask.

360
00:18:44,206 --> 00:18:46,416
Don't interrupt me while I'm eating.

361
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:48,544
Maybe you can do it
once I'm done, you know.

362
00:18:48,627 --> 00:18:50,295
I feel like they're just too excited.

363
00:18:50,379 --> 00:18:52,297
They probably think if
they're not going to do it now,

364
00:18:52,381 --> 00:18:54,299
they'd miss their chance.

365
00:18:54,383 --> 00:18:55,968
But trust us, we won't just disappear.

366
00:18:56,051 --> 00:19:00,013
We would appreciate it if
they would ask after we eat.

367
00:19:00,097 --> 00:19:02,182
That simple personal time

368
00:19:02,266 --> 00:19:05,227
is like our way of
just having our "me time."

369
00:19:05,310 --> 00:19:08,605
In a way, we get to regain this energy.

370
00:19:08,689 --> 00:19:13,068
That's why it's important
that we have that.

371
00:19:13,152 --> 00:19:15,195
Now that a lot of people are paying

372
00:19:15,279 --> 00:19:17,614
much, much more attention to us,

373
00:19:17,698 --> 00:19:20,117
it makes us move more carefully outside.

374
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:24,204
It gives me the creeps
when we're in public

375
00:19:24,288 --> 00:19:25,998
and it feels like we're being watched.

376
00:19:26,081 --> 00:19:27,875
Cameras are focused
on us a lot of the time.

377
00:19:27,958 --> 00:19:30,794
There were like four or
five of us BINI girls walking.

378
00:19:30,878 --> 00:19:32,212
It felt like we were being followed.

379
00:19:32,296 --> 00:19:34,464
And get this, it was a bunch of guys.

380
00:19:34,548 --> 00:19:36,216
We figured they were
going to ask for a photo.

381
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:37,718
So, we said, "Sorry, it's kind of late.

382
00:19:37,801 --> 00:19:38,927
Maybe next time?

383
00:19:39,011 --> 00:19:40,721
We just came from practice,
and we're tired."

384
00:19:40,804 --> 00:19:42,222
Then we continued walking.

385
00:19:42,306 --> 00:19:44,516
But they wouldn't take no for an answer.

386
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:46,810
We didn't want them to
find out where we lived

387
00:19:46,894 --> 00:19:48,687
if they kept following us.

388
00:19:49,229 --> 00:19:50,314
Of course, it's super creepy

389
00:19:50,397 --> 00:19:52,357
when someone you don't know
is following you.

390
00:19:52,441 --> 00:19:54,026
I mean, even if you're not a celebrity,

391
00:19:54,109 --> 00:19:57,196
it's scary when someone's tailing you

392
00:19:57,279 --> 00:20:01,742
or lurking around your place,
stalking you like that.

393
00:20:01,825 --> 00:20:04,411
I tried going to the bathroom,
but even before I was out,

394
00:20:04,494 --> 00:20:06,163
I could already hear someone
asking, ‘'Where's Aiah?

395
00:20:06,246 --> 00:20:07,497
Can I get a picture?"

396
00:20:07,581 --> 00:20:09,666
I was like, "Seriously?
Even in the bathroom?

397
00:20:09,750 --> 00:20:12,502
I'm still peeing!" [chuckling]

398
00:20:12,586 --> 00:20:14,588
Right now, we're still getting used to it.

399
00:20:14,671 --> 00:20:18,091
We can't really wrap
our heads around the idea

400
00:20:18,175 --> 00:20:21,970
that we're somehow famous.

401
00:20:24,181 --> 00:20:27,017
[reporter] <i>Filipino power
in a Thanksgiving concert</i>

402
00:20:27,100 --> 00:20:30,020
<i>at Araneta Coliseum this Friday night!</i>

403
00:20:30,103 --> 00:20:36,985
[vocalizing]

404
00:20:53,252 --> 00:20:55,295
[crowd cheering]

405
00:20:59,007 --> 00:21:01,927
It's Staku's birthday!

406
00:21:02,010 --> 00:21:05,305
[singing] <i>♪ Happy birthday, Staku ♪</i>

407
00:21:05,389 --> 00:21:06,723
21!

408
00:21:06,807 --> 00:21:11,103
This year, I think I've become
a lot more confident.

409
00:21:11,186 --> 00:21:14,189
<i>Before, you could say I had no spine.</i>

410
00:21:14,273 --> 00:21:16,900
I didn't have the courage to
speak up, even to the girls.

411
00:21:16,984 --> 00:21:19,820
I couldn't tell them how I felt.

412
00:21:19,903 --> 00:21:22,572
I promised myself that
I'm done with this attitude.

413
00:21:22,656 --> 00:21:24,116
<i>Enough with the low self-esteem.</i>

414
00:21:24,199 --> 00:21:26,410
It's better if you focus
on feeding yourself

415
00:21:26,493 --> 00:21:28,704
positive vibes like, "You're doing great.

416
00:21:28,787 --> 00:21:31,290
You're beautiful. You're smart."

417
00:21:31,832 --> 00:21:33,500
We're all becoming adults, actually.

418
00:21:33,583 --> 00:21:36,420
I feel we're really getting there,

419
00:21:36,503 --> 00:21:38,380
becoming more mature.

420
00:21:38,463 --> 00:21:39,381
I wouldn't be surprised
if in the next interview,

421
00:21:39,464 --> 00:21:40,424
we'd be introducing our husbands and kids.

422
00:21:40,507 --> 00:21:41,591
[laughs]

423
00:21:42,384 --> 00:21:44,428
[Stacey] <i>I grew up as an only child.</i>

424
00:21:44,511 --> 00:21:45,721
<i>My mom raised me on her own.</i>

425
00:21:45,804 --> 00:21:50,851
It was just the two of us,
plus my grandpa helped out.

426
00:21:50,934 --> 00:21:52,602
She must have struggled sometimes,

427
00:21:52,686 --> 00:21:55,230
but she never let it show.

428
00:21:55,314 --> 00:21:59,526
It's okay because my mom's
really strong as a person.

429
00:21:59,609 --> 00:22:02,696
She's the ultimate girly girl.
She's obsessed with pink.

430
00:22:02,779 --> 00:22:04,072
I totally get my girly side from her.

431
00:22:04,156 --> 00:22:05,824
<i>Well, there's no other option, is there?</i>

432
00:22:05,907 --> 00:22:08,201
She asked me if I wanted to meet my dad.

433
00:22:08,285 --> 00:22:10,495
<i>I told her, "Of course, but let's wait</i>

434
00:22:10,579 --> 00:22:12,497
<i>until I'm very successful."</i>

435
00:22:12,581 --> 00:22:15,459
<i>When I've proven myself,
then I'll face him.</i>

436
00:22:15,542 --> 00:22:18,628
I never really felt like I was
missing out on having a dad.

437
00:22:18,712 --> 00:22:21,673
The love I get from my family,

438
00:22:21,757 --> 00:22:23,592
<i>especially my mom,
my grandpa, and my aunts,</i>

439
00:22:23,675 --> 00:22:25,844
is just so amazing.

440
00:22:25,927 --> 00:22:27,637
[Ivy] <i>You can really feel it.</i>

441
00:22:27,721 --> 00:22:32,601
It's like you know that
she is destined to be someone.

442
00:22:32,684 --> 00:22:37,022
<i>Growing up, she loved singing,
dancing, and rapping.</i>

443
00:22:37,105 --> 00:22:41,985
[performing "Salamin, Salamin"]

444
00:22:42,069 --> 00:22:44,863
And now, she's living the beautiful dream.

445
00:22:44,946 --> 00:22:50,243
[mellow music playing]

446
00:22:50,327 --> 00:22:52,496
I'm getting all emotional [sniffles]

447
00:22:52,579 --> 00:22:54,498
because this was just a dream before.

448
00:22:54,581 --> 00:22:57,000
<i>And now, it'sactually happening.</i>

449
00:22:57,084 --> 00:22:59,795
<i>I'm so grateful to God</i>

450
00:22:59,878 --> 00:23:04,466
for putting this dream in our hearts.

451
00:23:04,549 --> 00:23:07,594
<i>Staku and I are super close.</i>

452
00:23:07,677 --> 00:23:09,596
<i>She's a total mama's girl.</i>

453
00:23:09,679 --> 00:23:14,810
<i>I'm starting to get usedto us
not being together all the time</i>

454
00:23:14,893 --> 00:23:17,270
<i>nowthat she has a career.</i>

455
00:23:17,354 --> 00:23:18,688
Whenever she's sick though,

456
00:23:18,772 --> 00:23:21,191
I drop everything and come to her.

457
00:23:21,274 --> 00:23:24,152
I call her non-stop and check in on her

458
00:23:24,236 --> 00:23:27,531
<i>when she's not feeling well.</i>

459
00:23:27,614 --> 00:23:29,199
<i>But she's tough.</i>

460
00:23:29,282 --> 00:23:32,119
<i>She's a strong girl,
even stronger than me.</i>

461
00:23:32,202 --> 00:23:34,287
She doesn't know it, but she's my idol.

462
00:23:34,371 --> 00:23:35,247
[chuckles]

463
00:23:35,330 --> 00:23:39,292
<i>When you're a mom, you are
your child's number one fan.</i>

464
00:23:42,462 --> 00:23:49,094
[performing "Salamin, Salamin"]

465
00:23:57,394 --> 00:23:59,396
[Mikha] <i>Actually, even when
we were still in Baguio,</i>

466
00:23:59,479 --> 00:24:02,858
I was already complaining about my knee.

467
00:24:02,941 --> 00:24:04,985
How it hurts every time
I bend it and straighten it

468
00:24:05,068 --> 00:24:07,571
<i>or when I put my weight on it.</i>

469
00:24:07,654 --> 00:24:10,699
After Baguio, the pain was at its peak.

470
00:24:10,782 --> 00:24:12,492
I was like, "Something's wrong,
I can't walk."

471
00:24:12,576 --> 00:24:15,704
<i>When I got home, we had a rest day.</i>

472
00:24:15,787 --> 00:24:18,790
And fortunately, my sister
and brother were there

473
00:24:18,874 --> 00:24:20,167
during that time.

474
00:24:20,250 --> 00:24:22,127
The pain was severe so we ended up going
to the emergency room.

475
00:24:22,210 --> 00:24:23,503
<i>They had to observe me,</i>

476
00:24:23,587 --> 00:24:25,505
<i>so I was confined in the hospital.</i>

477
00:24:25,589 --> 00:24:27,591
<i>Surprise, surprise!</i>

478
00:24:27,674 --> 00:24:29,718
Everyone was like, "What?"

479
00:24:29,801 --> 00:24:32,304
[performing "Salamin, Salamin"]

480
00:24:32,846 --> 00:24:35,390
When we saw her in the crowd
during the performance,

481
00:24:35,473 --> 00:24:38,435
I was like, "Why's Mikha crying?
What is she crying about?"

482
00:24:38,518 --> 00:24:45,192
[performing "Salamin, Salamin"]

483
00:24:46,484 --> 00:24:49,279
It's different when you're watching them.

484
00:24:50,989 --> 00:24:52,199
I don't know.

485
00:24:53,450 --> 00:24:56,286
I was like, "Okay, I want
to watch BINI's performance."

486
00:24:56,369 --> 00:24:57,829
I was like, "Damn."

487
00:24:57,913 --> 00:25:00,707
It's different when you see
the crowd from the stage.

488
00:25:00,790 --> 00:25:03,793
[Mikha] <i>But when you see the whole arena,</i>

489
00:25:03,877 --> 00:25:06,004
<i>and them on stage...</i>

490
00:25:06,087 --> 00:25:07,797
<i>So I was just really overwhelmed.</i>

491
00:25:07,881 --> 00:25:10,300
You know, I don't want to sound cocky.

492
00:25:10,383 --> 00:25:12,344
I was so proud of the girls at that time.

493
00:25:14,679 --> 00:25:18,516
[Sheena] <i>Oh, Miks! She's a baddie.</i>

494
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:20,977
<i>Wait, no. She's not a baddie.</i>

495
00:25:21,061 --> 00:25:22,145
<i>She's a softie.</i>

496
00:25:22,229 --> 00:25:23,688
<i>She should be in the
sob squad too, you know.</i>

497
00:25:23,772 --> 00:25:28,109
<i>People see her as
nonchalant and unbothered.</i>

498
00:25:28,193 --> 00:25:29,694
<i>But when it comes to us girls,</i>

499
00:25:29,778 --> 00:25:33,740
<i>she's very vocal and emotional.</i>

500
00:25:33,823 --> 00:25:35,408
I find it very sweet.

501
00:25:35,492 --> 00:25:37,535
Thank you, Miks, because she rarely cries.

502
00:25:38,578 --> 00:25:39,788
[Mikha] <i>I was born in Cebu</i>

503
00:25:39,871 --> 00:25:43,750
<i>and then I moved to Santa Rosa, Laguna.</i>

504
00:25:43,833 --> 00:25:47,087
<i>And then I moved to Silang, Cavite.</i>

505
00:25:47,170 --> 00:25:51,216
<i>And then I moved
to Quezon City temporarily</i>

506
00:25:51,299 --> 00:25:52,968
<i>because we were waiting for</i>

507
00:25:53,051 --> 00:25:55,887
our house in San Juan to be built.

508
00:25:57,722 --> 00:25:59,224
Did you memorize it?

509
00:25:59,307 --> 00:26:01,685
I didn't like it, honestly.

510
00:26:01,768 --> 00:26:04,688
Because if I compare myself
with my other classmates,

511
00:26:04,771 --> 00:26:06,189
my other batchmates, they're like, "Oh!

512
00:26:06,273 --> 00:26:07,732
This girl was my childhood friend."

513
00:26:07,816 --> 00:26:10,026
I was like, I don't even know
what that feels like.

514
00:26:10,694 --> 00:26:13,029
[Mikha] <i>BINI, for me,
was like my childhood.</i>

515
00:26:13,989 --> 00:26:15,615
<i>Or like, let's say teenage years.</i>

516
00:26:15,699 --> 00:26:19,202
<i>I really feel like I grew in BINI.</i>

517
00:26:19,286 --> 00:26:21,204
I changed a lot in BINI.

518
00:26:22,664 --> 00:26:25,166
I feel like there were many ups and downs.

519
00:26:25,250 --> 00:26:30,880
<i>More downs, actually, before
things started picking up.</i>

520
00:26:32,465 --> 00:26:35,302
Of course, that's normal.

521
00:26:36,094 --> 00:26:38,179
And it made me into the person I am now.

522
00:26:40,724 --> 00:26:45,312
[MYRLA] <i>Mikha, from when she was little,</i>

523
00:26:45,395 --> 00:26:48,940
<i>always loved singing and dancing.</i>

524
00:26:50,900 --> 00:26:54,904
She's never been shy about performing,

525
00:26:54,988 --> 00:26:59,451
even in school programs or talent shows.

526
00:26:59,534 --> 00:27:01,453
<i>I'm very proudand grateful</i>

527
00:27:01,536 --> 00:27:03,872
<i>for what ishappening to Mikha and BINI.</i>

528
00:27:04,581 --> 00:27:06,499
[fan] <i>Hey! Hi, Mikha!</i>

529
00:27:07,584 --> 00:27:10,170
There was a time when she was
confined to the hospital

530
00:27:10,253 --> 00:27:11,796
because of allergies.

531
00:27:11,880 --> 00:27:12,922
Her eyes were swollen.

532
00:27:13,006 --> 00:27:16,760
Late at night, she kept
begging her managers

533
00:27:16,843 --> 00:27:21,056
to allow her to perform.

534
00:27:21,139 --> 00:27:23,058
She doesn't want to miss it.

535
00:27:23,141 --> 00:27:25,518
[Myrla] <i>I was worried more
about her health.</i>

536
00:27:25,602 --> 00:27:27,687
Actually, all she had to do
was message me, "Ma,"

537
00:27:28,480 --> 00:27:29,981
followed by a sad face.

538
00:27:31,441 --> 00:27:36,071
And I'd already know.
I'm stressed out already.

539
00:27:36,696 --> 00:27:39,699
It doesn't help that we live in Bicol.

540
00:27:41,076 --> 00:27:43,787
<i>So you would want to fly where she is.</i>

541
00:27:43,870 --> 00:27:49,667
I'd tell her to wait for me,
"Mom's coming".

542
00:27:54,923 --> 00:27:57,675
I'm excited because I want
to see how Blooms will react.

543
00:27:57,759 --> 00:27:59,761
It's the first time this will happen,

544
00:27:59,844 --> 00:28:02,180
and it's like God is telling me,

545
00:28:02,263 --> 00:28:06,267
I can't miss this live performance.

546
00:28:07,435 --> 00:28:09,104
That was a big surprise.

547
00:28:09,187 --> 00:28:11,398
They were like, "Okay.

548
00:28:11,481 --> 00:28:12,899
They want you to join them.

549
00:28:12,982 --> 00:28:15,026
<i>You don't have to dance.</i>

550
00:28:15,110 --> 00:28:19,447
Because it's just a walk.
Just be careful."

551
00:28:21,324 --> 00:28:27,997
[somber music playing]

552
00:28:43,471 --> 00:28:45,598
[Jhoanna] <i>So, of course,
we still had a lot of rehearsals</i>

553
00:28:45,682 --> 00:28:47,183
<i>in between all those shoots.</i>

554
00:28:47,267 --> 00:28:50,103
<i>I wasn't aware that the girls
were already falling ill.</i>

555
00:28:50,186 --> 00:28:52,647
[Sheena] <i>Every day, we're either
filming, doing a photoshoot,</i>

556
00:28:52,731 --> 00:28:53,857
<i>or shooting a music video.</i>

557
00:28:53,940 --> 00:28:57,110
<i>We've set a high standard for ourselves</i>

558
00:28:57,193 --> 00:28:59,946
<i>because, like, BINI
isalready amazing, right?</i>

559
00:29:00,029 --> 00:29:04,033
<i>But if we want to go global,
we have to level up even more.</i>

560
00:29:04,117 --> 00:29:05,910
<i>We're not just working twice as hard,</i>

561
00:29:05,994 --> 00:29:07,704
<i>we're putting in thrice the effort.</i>

562
00:29:07,787 --> 00:29:08,997
[Jhoanna] <i>It's not like
we're just slacking off</i>

563
00:29:09,080 --> 00:29:11,499
<i>when no one's looking.</i>

564
00:29:12,292 --> 00:29:14,502
[Stacey] <i>We're super game
to do the hard work.</i>

565
00:29:15,086 --> 00:29:16,713
<i>Sure, you might hear us whine a little.</i>

566
00:29:16,796 --> 00:29:21,092
<i>But at the end of the day,
we know that we love what we do.</i>

567
00:29:21,176 --> 00:29:28,099
[somber music continues]

568
00:29:28,933 --> 00:29:30,518
Before our concert in Cebu,

569
00:29:30,602 --> 00:29:32,604
our schedule was really hectic.

570
00:29:32,687 --> 00:29:33,813
We had no rest.

571
00:29:33,897 --> 00:29:37,442
Our schedule was packed
with shoots, brand shoots.

572
00:29:37,525 --> 00:29:39,903
So that day we went to the airport,

573
00:29:39,986 --> 00:29:41,404
we were all nursing coughs and colds.

574
00:29:41,488 --> 00:29:45,909
[Aiah] <i>So, for health reasons
and just to be safe,</i>

575
00:29:45,992 --> 00:29:48,036
<i>we would want to be covered up.</i>

576
00:29:48,119 --> 00:29:52,290
We didn't expect a huge crowd
to be waiting for us there.

577
00:29:52,832 --> 00:29:54,709
Of course, you're just flying to Cebu.

578
00:29:54,793 --> 00:29:55,752
You're not gonna be
red-carpet-ready for that.

579
00:29:55,835 --> 00:29:57,921
[indistinct chatter]

580
00:29:58,588 --> 00:30:00,215
[Jhoanna] <i>We weren't made up.</i>

581
00:30:00,298 --> 00:30:03,635
So we wore masks,
shades and baseball caps.

582
00:30:03,718 --> 00:30:06,012
It's what we usually do, even before.

583
00:30:06,095 --> 00:30:07,305
[Sheena] <i>There are some folks</i>

584
00:30:07,388 --> 00:30:10,517
<i>who'd start snapping pictures
of us snoozing on the plane.</i>

585
00:30:11,100 --> 00:30:12,852
Good thing we weren't caught
with our mouths open!

586
00:30:12,936 --> 00:30:15,897
They'd record us this way
while we slept like this.

587
00:30:15,980 --> 00:30:18,775
[thrilling music playing]

588
00:30:18,858 --> 00:30:22,403
[people cheering]

589
00:30:30,453 --> 00:30:32,997
[Colet] <i>We landed in Cebu
to a sea of people!</i>

590
00:30:35,875 --> 00:30:37,293
- <i>Shucks!
- There were so many people.</i>

591
00:30:37,377 --> 00:30:40,213
<i>I panicked a little</i>

592
00:30:40,296 --> 00:30:42,048
seeing all those people waiting for us

593
00:30:42,131 --> 00:30:43,675
and that early in the morning too.

594
00:30:44,843 --> 00:30:48,221
The crowd was huge and it was wild.

595
00:30:48,304 --> 00:30:52,350
[crowd cheering]

596
00:30:52,433 --> 00:30:54,727
We were acknowledging them,
giving them our best smiles,

597
00:30:54,811 --> 00:30:56,688
even though you couldn't
really see it with our masks on.

598
00:30:56,771 --> 00:30:58,398
We were super grateful.

599
00:30:58,481 --> 00:31:01,526
I was really excited to perform in Cebu

600
00:31:01,609 --> 00:31:04,112
because I have a ton of friends there.

601
00:31:04,195 --> 00:31:07,198
The girls kept teasing me, saying

602
00:31:07,282 --> 00:31:09,868
it was going to be
"Aiah and Friends" in Cebu.

603
00:31:09,951 --> 00:31:12,829
<i>You know, Cebu being my home turf.</i>

604
00:31:12,912 --> 00:31:14,747
[overlapping screaming]

605
00:31:14,831 --> 00:31:21,588
[crowd cheering]

606
00:31:22,630 --> 00:31:24,215
[Jhoanna] <i>The next day,</i>

607
00:31:24,299 --> 00:31:27,093
you see all these comments like
"Who do they think they are?"

608
00:31:27,176 --> 00:31:30,305
"K-pop wannabes!
Why are they wearing masks?

609
00:31:30,388 --> 00:31:31,723
There's no need for it!"

610
00:31:31,806 --> 00:31:33,099
[Jhoanna] <i>Acting like big shots!</i>

611
00:31:33,182 --> 00:31:34,350
<i>Feeling like they're stars!</i>

612
00:31:34,434 --> 00:31:35,560
As if their presence
would cause a commotion."

613
00:31:35,643 --> 00:31:37,520
They were comparing us to other artists...

614
00:31:37,604 --> 00:31:39,856
[Gwen] <i>Even a regular person has a choice</i>

615
00:31:39,939 --> 00:31:42,275
to wear a face mask and a cap
anytime they want, am I right?

616
00:31:42,358 --> 00:31:44,152
I have no idea what was going on.

617
00:31:44,235 --> 00:31:45,945
I was like, "What? What's this?"

618
00:31:46,029 --> 00:31:47,447
Oh seriously. Lord!

619
00:31:47,530 --> 00:31:48,823
Another day, another issue!

620
00:31:48,907 --> 00:31:51,784
I get it, people are gonna talk.

621
00:31:51,868 --> 00:31:53,745
You can't please everybody.

622
00:31:53,828 --> 00:31:55,622
[Colet] <i>But the part
that really gets to me</i>

623
00:31:55,705 --> 00:31:58,207
<i>is that it's becoming the norm for people</i>

624
00:31:58,291 --> 00:32:00,668
to be so quick to judge
when they don't even know you.

625
00:32:00,752 --> 00:32:02,754
[Sheena] <i>My mindset at the time
was like,"I'll ignore them."</i>

626
00:32:02,837 --> 00:32:04,339
<i>It's not true, anyway.</i>

627
00:32:04,422 --> 00:32:06,132
<i>And like, what's their source?</i>

628
00:32:06,215 --> 00:32:07,258
A picture?

629
00:32:07,342 --> 00:32:08,426
You can tell how I really am
through a picture?

630
00:32:08,509 --> 00:32:10,595
So clever. Not.

631
00:32:12,138 --> 00:32:14,474
I was like, "Okay. You're on."

632
00:32:18,937 --> 00:32:20,605
[Colet] <i>What's it like
to grow up in Bohol?</i>

633
00:32:20,688 --> 00:32:22,982
<i>So, my father's in a band, right?</i>

634
00:32:23,066 --> 00:32:28,237
And every morning, he'd blast
Air Supply and Journey.

635
00:32:28,321 --> 00:32:31,240
[Colet] <i>Those are the songs
I grew up listening.</i>

636
00:32:34,285 --> 00:32:35,703
Papa was the drummer in his band.

637
00:32:35,787 --> 00:32:36,788
So, sometimes I'd hang out with them,

638
00:32:36,871 --> 00:32:41,834
<i>and even sit in
on their practice sessions.</i>

639
00:32:41,918 --> 00:32:44,587
That's how I spent my childhood.

640
00:32:44,671 --> 00:32:47,674
[Gina] <i>She's really shy, sir.</i>

641
00:32:48,383 --> 00:32:52,512
She doesn't go out much

642
00:32:52,595 --> 00:32:55,807
because she's afraid
we'll get angry at her.

643
00:32:55,890 --> 00:32:59,185
Before, she was too timid

644
00:32:59,686 --> 00:33:04,190
to wear anything revealing,

645
00:33:04,273 --> 00:33:07,193
like sleeveless tops or shorts.

646
00:33:07,276 --> 00:33:08,194
[Lokins] <i>Always in pajamas.</i>

647
00:33:08,277 --> 00:33:14,909
[Gina] <i>Pajamas. I remember there
was this local beauty pageant.</i>

648
00:33:14,993 --> 00:33:17,829
<i>She was handpicked
to represent the barangay.</i>

649
00:33:17,912 --> 00:33:19,622
But she asked if she could wear pajamas

650
00:33:19,706 --> 00:33:21,708
because she wasn't used
to sporting crop tops.

651
00:33:21,791 --> 00:33:23,251
[chuckles]

652
00:33:24,502 --> 00:33:27,088
We were always at each other's throats...
[laughs]

653
00:33:27,171 --> 00:33:30,591
...especially with six kids in the house.

654
00:33:30,675 --> 00:33:34,554
I'm sure our neighbors could hear us

655
00:33:34,637 --> 00:33:38,141
yelling at each other from a mile away.

656
00:33:38,224 --> 00:33:41,310
So, we're not really
the mushy type, you know?

657
00:33:41,394 --> 00:33:43,312
[Colet] <i>We don't really
express it with words.</i>

658
00:33:43,396 --> 00:33:44,981
We show it through our actions.

659
00:33:46,399 --> 00:33:52,780
[indistinct chatter]

660
00:33:52,864 --> 00:33:54,490
So right now, BINI will be welcomed

661
00:33:54,574 --> 00:33:56,117
upon their arrival in Cebu.

662
00:33:56,200 --> 00:33:57,702
Before they do stage blocking,

663
00:33:57,785 --> 00:34:01,914
the people from Waterfront have
prepared a welcome for them.

664
00:34:01,998 --> 00:34:04,167
Let's see how they'll do it.

665
00:34:04,250 --> 00:34:11,132
[cultural music playing]

666
00:34:26,272 --> 00:34:31,694
[bold music playing]

667
00:34:31,778 --> 00:34:38,576
[crowd cheering]

668
00:34:39,786 --> 00:34:46,209
[bold music continues]

669
00:34:46,292 --> 00:34:49,212
[vocalizing]

670
00:34:56,677 --> 00:34:58,513
[Mikha] <i>I was very excited
to perform in Cebu</i>

671
00:34:58,596 --> 00:35:00,807
because I was just coming from

672
00:35:00,890 --> 00:35:04,102
an injury and I was finally
allowed to perform.

673
00:35:04,811 --> 00:35:07,480
Actually, I was born in Cebu

674
00:35:08,689 --> 00:35:10,191
but I don't know how to speak <i>Bisaya.</i>

675
00:35:10,274 --> 00:35:11,609
I'm very sorry.

676
00:35:11,692 --> 00:35:14,112
[Colet] <i>They're the ones
who came to me, asking me</i>

677
00:35:14,195 --> 00:35:16,614
"Colet, how do you say this?"

678
00:35:16,697 --> 00:35:17,907
What's up, <i>mananap?</i>

679
00:35:17,990 --> 00:35:19,117
[Mikha] What's up, <i>mananap?</i>

680
00:35:19,200 --> 00:35:21,452
[Mikha] Really? Maybe that's
something else...

681
00:35:21,536 --> 00:35:22,453
No, I swear!

682
00:35:22,537 --> 00:35:24,122
She said that it's cute.

683
00:35:24,205 --> 00:35:26,791
So I said, "Say, What's up, <i>mananap?</i>

684
00:35:26,874 --> 00:35:28,709
[Mikha] What's up, <i>mananap?</i>

685
00:35:28,793 --> 00:35:30,211
[Mikha] It's Mikha!

686
00:35:30,294 --> 00:35:32,380
[crowd cheers]

687
00:35:32,463 --> 00:35:35,007
She's such a liar.

688
00:35:35,091 --> 00:35:36,801
It's like a joke.

689
00:35:38,094 --> 00:35:39,387
Um, Aiah, what is <i>mananap?</i>

690
00:35:39,470 --> 00:35:42,390
Um, <i>mananap</i> is an insect. [giggles]

691
00:35:43,099 --> 00:35:43,933
It's not.

692
00:35:44,016 --> 00:35:45,852
It's cute that they're making an effort

693
00:35:45,935 --> 00:35:47,103
to learn a new language

694
00:35:47,186 --> 00:35:49,689
just to make the Blooms
in attendance happy.

695
00:35:49,772 --> 00:35:51,524
Yeah. Thanks, Colet! [chuckles]

696
00:35:51,607 --> 00:35:55,361
[singing "Salamin, Salamin"]

697
00:35:55,444 --> 00:35:59,699
INAUDIBLE MUSIC PLAYING

698
00:35:59,782 --> 00:36:01,951
[singing the Cebuano of
"Liwanag Sa Dilim"]

699
00:36:02,034 --> 00:36:04,829
[Stacey] Everybody! If you can answer--

700
00:36:04,912 --> 00:36:06,706
Bebe, give me a dream for later...

701
00:36:07,248 --> 00:36:08,833
[in Cebuano] Cebu, make some noise!

702
00:36:08,916 --> 00:36:11,544
[vocalizing]

703
00:36:11,627 --> 00:36:12,879
[in Cebuano] I am not...

704
00:36:14,881 --> 00:36:15,923
[in Cebuano] I am not hungry...

705
00:36:16,007 --> 00:36:17,425
I am not hungry...

706
00:36:17,508 --> 00:36:18,718
[Colet in Cebuano] I love the coconut.

707
00:36:18,801 --> 00:36:20,011
[chuckles]

708
00:36:20,094 --> 00:36:21,971
[Maloi in Cebuano] I love the coconut?

709
00:36:22,054 --> 00:36:24,390
Do you know how to speak <i>Bisaya</i>?

710
00:36:24,473 --> 00:36:25,516
What's the <i>Bisaya</i> of

711
00:36:25,600 --> 00:36:26,767
"Do you know how to speak <i>Bisaya?</i>"

712
00:36:26,851 --> 00:36:29,812
I get to take a break when

713
00:36:29,896 --> 00:36:32,148
we're in a Visayan-speaking province.

714
00:36:32,231 --> 00:36:34,942
Yes! I can breathe a sigh of relief too.

715
00:36:35,026 --> 00:36:41,115
Once I'm in my Visayan mode,
I can't shut up.

716
00:36:41,199 --> 00:36:43,409
I get to have our own world that time.

717
00:36:46,370 --> 00:36:49,999
[Aiah] <i>I asked them if they
couldswing by backstage.</i>

718
00:36:50,082 --> 00:36:54,128
<i>I just need a little boost
before I perform.</i>

719
00:36:55,087 --> 00:36:57,089
And guess what?

720
00:36:57,173 --> 00:36:58,257
Wish granted.

721
00:36:58,341 --> 00:37:02,470
[soft music playing]

722
00:37:02,553 --> 00:37:04,722
As my older brother,
he's really proud of me.

723
00:37:04,805 --> 00:37:08,809
It's us two, so we just
love each other as siblings.

724
00:37:11,687 --> 00:37:13,689
[Aiah] <i>When it comes to my family,</i>

725
00:37:13,773 --> 00:37:16,484
<i>I can't say that
I was the most open person.</i>

726
00:37:16,567 --> 00:37:18,236
So I wasn't super close with my family.

727
00:37:18,319 --> 00:37:21,155
Even though there's just
me and my brother,

728
00:37:21,239 --> 00:37:22,490
[Aiah] <i>plus my parents,
so that makes four.</i>

729
00:37:22,573 --> 00:37:24,617
But still, I would keep things to myself.

730
00:37:24,700 --> 00:37:25,701
Until, all of a sudden,

731
00:37:25,785 --> 00:37:30,039
I don't know what came over me,

732
00:37:30,122 --> 00:37:31,916
but I wanted to try modeling.

733
00:37:31,999 --> 00:37:35,211
It was like a way to boost my confidence.

734
00:37:35,294 --> 00:37:37,213
And it went from there.

735
00:37:40,508 --> 00:37:41,509
[Dick Arceta] <i>When she turned 17,</i>

736
00:37:41,592 --> 00:37:43,552
she really wanted to try
living on her own.

737
00:37:45,596 --> 00:37:50,476
We told her, "Go for it!
We'll always be here for you."

738
00:37:51,394 --> 00:37:52,895
So on her 18th birthday,

739
00:37:52,979 --> 00:37:54,897
she packed her bag and
moved to Manila all by herself.

740
00:37:54,981 --> 00:37:56,732
Of course, I had my hesitations.

741
00:37:56,816 --> 00:37:58,526
But she wanted to prove she could do it.

742
00:38:02,571 --> 00:38:04,699
As a mother, I worried when
she had a bout of anxiety.

743
00:38:04,782 --> 00:38:07,034
[giggles softly] Of course, I'm a mother.

744
00:38:08,077 --> 00:38:10,955
We were so worried
that she couldn't handle it.

745
00:38:11,038 --> 00:38:15,376
<i>It was a mix of stress, pressure,</i>

746
00:38:16,544 --> 00:38:18,713
and that feeling of being
alone with no one to talk to.

747
00:38:18,796 --> 00:38:22,508
[soft music playing]

748
00:38:22,591 --> 00:38:23,926
We decided on the spot that

749
00:38:24,010 --> 00:38:26,012
her mom would go to her in Manila.

750
00:38:26,095 --> 00:38:27,054
That helped.

751
00:38:27,138 --> 00:38:30,558
She hugged me for a really long time.

752
00:38:30,641 --> 00:38:32,351
I was trying to cheer her up
while I was there

753
00:38:32,435 --> 00:38:36,147
so she started to enjoy herself.

754
00:38:36,230 --> 00:38:37,148
Aiah's a fighter!

755
00:38:37,231 --> 00:38:39,775
Over time, I blossomed, I bloomed.

756
00:38:39,859 --> 00:38:45,489
I'm very happy that I'm back here

757
00:38:45,573 --> 00:38:49,952
because the room is filled
with love and support.

758
00:38:50,036 --> 00:38:53,539
Actually, the pressure was on in Cebu.

759
00:38:53,622 --> 00:38:58,294
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

760
00:38:58,377 --> 00:39:01,589
[Aiah] <i>I wanted to impress
my childhood friends,</i>

761
00:39:01,672 --> 00:39:05,801
my teachers, and even those
people who bullied me.

762
00:39:05,885 --> 00:39:07,720
It was like this is my time to shine.

763
00:39:07,803 --> 00:39:10,306
It's my home! Watch me!

764
00:39:10,389 --> 00:39:11,974
[chuckles]

765
00:39:12,058 --> 00:39:13,726
[crowd cheers]

766
00:39:13,809 --> 00:39:20,775
["Huwag Muna Tayong Umuwi" playing]

767
00:39:36,791 --> 00:39:43,798
["Huwag Muna Tayong Umuwi"
continues playing]

768
00:40:01,273 --> 00:40:08,280
[tense music playing]

769
00:40:13,035 --> 00:40:14,829
[crowd cheering]

770
00:40:23,587 --> 00:40:25,089
[Jhoanna] <i>I was good
during the performance.</i>

771
00:40:25,172 --> 00:40:26,715
[Jhoanna] <i>But I started feeling sick</i>

772
00:40:26,799 --> 00:40:28,300
<i>when we reached the dressing room.</i>

773
00:40:28,384 --> 00:40:30,719
<i>I was so weak, I couldn't get
myself off the floor.</i>

774
00:40:32,888 --> 00:40:35,891
[Mikha] <i>I get so worried
when one of us gets sick.</i>

775
00:40:35,975 --> 00:40:37,726
<i>Because after everything,</i>

776
00:40:37,810 --> 00:40:39,895
<i>all we really have is each other.</i>

777
00:40:43,482 --> 00:40:45,151
[producer] Who's her roommate?

778
00:40:45,234 --> 00:40:51,490
[Stacey] <i>We always pray that
none of us get sick</i>

779
00:40:51,574 --> 00:40:53,659
<i>even if we know we're pushing our limits.</i>

780
00:40:53,742 --> 00:40:57,121
[Maan Manauis] Yes, we already
we already gave the electric fan.

781
00:40:57,204 --> 00:41:02,501
It's almost <i>Pantropiko</i> and
it's almost the end of the concert.

782
00:41:02,585 --> 00:41:05,421
[Stacey] <i>So it worries us
when someone gets sick.</i>

783
00:41:05,504 --> 00:41:09,800
<i>We always try to push ourselves
to the best of our abilities.</i>

784
00:41:09,884 --> 00:41:12,845
[Maan Manauis]
Jovy is in the
room with Stacey and Jhoanna.

785
00:41:12,928 --> 00:41:14,805
I'm now here with Gwen.

786
00:41:19,018 --> 00:41:21,687
[Jhoanna] <i>I get really dizzy easily</i>

787
00:41:21,770 --> 00:41:24,607
<i>especially from lights and loud noises.</i>

788
00:41:28,569 --> 00:41:30,613
[Jhoanna] <i>My head was spinning</i>

789
00:41:30,696 --> 00:41:36,619
<i>even though my eyes
were closed and the lights</i>

790
00:41:36,702 --> 00:41:39,163
<i>were already dimmed at the hotel.</i>

791
00:41:39,246 --> 00:41:45,586
[tense music playing]

792
00:41:49,548 --> 00:41:51,217
It should be tied, or hidden.

793
00:41:51,300 --> 00:41:52,760
Oh it fits me perfectly!

794
00:41:53,469 --> 00:41:56,722
[shrieks and laughs]
["Strings" by BINI playing]

795
00:41:56,805 --> 00:41:58,974
[Sheena] Oh my God.

796
00:42:01,685 --> 00:42:08,692
["Strings" continues playing]

797
00:42:10,110 --> 00:42:12,446
Uh... oh my God.

798
00:42:12,530 --> 00:42:14,114
About a week after...

799
00:42:14,198 --> 00:42:17,201
Colet is totally the mastermind
of the Jabbawockeez stunt!

800
00:42:17,284 --> 00:42:19,495
She is the brains behind that plan.
[laughs]

801
00:42:19,578 --> 00:42:21,205
[Jhoanna] <i>Colet was just joking around,</i>

802
00:42:21,288 --> 00:42:24,708
<i>like, "Why don't we try this?"
The idea actually came from the Blooms.</i>

803
00:42:24,792 --> 00:42:27,336
I think they saw somewhere
someone suggesting

804
00:42:27,419 --> 00:42:29,672
"What if BINI wore Jabbawockeez masks?"

805
00:42:29,755 --> 00:42:31,757
If you can't stop them, join them.

806
00:42:31,840 --> 00:42:38,806
["Strings" by BINI playing]

807
00:42:45,145 --> 00:42:47,022
I'm usually nice to people,

808
00:42:47,106 --> 00:42:50,401
but when people go too far,

809
00:42:50,943 --> 00:42:53,487
especially when they're lying,
I'm not going to let it slide.

810
00:42:53,571 --> 00:42:54,488
<i>I'll clap back,</i>

811
00:42:54,572 --> 00:42:56,490
<i>even if I get in trouble with the bosses.</i>

812
00:42:56,574 --> 00:42:58,075
[Colet chuckles]

813
00:42:58,158 --> 00:43:02,788
So I went to our group chat
and said, "Girls, back me up."

814
00:43:02,871 --> 00:43:04,790
I was like, "Go, let's do it."
Everyone was in.

815
00:43:04,873 --> 00:43:10,087
Because we were all so annoyed
by the fake stuff we'd been reading.

816
00:43:10,170 --> 00:43:11,171
I was down for it.

817
00:43:11,255 --> 00:43:12,298
Even though I'm nonchalant,
I'm okay to do it.

818
00:43:12,381 --> 00:43:14,049
Bet it'll be fun too. [chuckles]

819
00:43:14,133 --> 00:43:20,389
["Strings" by BINI playing]

820
00:43:20,472 --> 00:43:22,516
Most of the time, when
something like this happens,

821
00:43:22,600 --> 00:43:24,226
there's always one person who disagrees.

822
00:43:24,310 --> 00:43:28,022
But since the majority rules,
we go with it.

823
00:43:28,105 --> 00:43:31,692
But this time,
everyone was totally on board.

824
00:43:31,775 --> 00:43:33,819
They won't stop saying stuff about us.

825
00:43:33,902 --> 00:43:38,032
So, if they make fun of you,
a little clapback wouldn't hurt.

826
00:43:38,115 --> 00:43:41,201
["Strings" by BINI playing]

827
00:43:41,285 --> 00:43:43,954
"BINI's Jabbawockeez-inspired
outfits at the airport are trending"

828
00:43:44,038 --> 00:43:47,625
"BINI claps back at bashers
through Jabbawockeez-inspired look"

829
00:43:47,708 --> 00:43:50,919
["Strings" continues]

830
00:43:51,003 --> 00:43:52,171
[camera shutter clicks]

831
00:43:54,048 --> 00:43:56,925
[camera shutter clicks]

832
00:43:57,009 --> 00:43:58,927
It was Colet who actually
bought the masks.

833
00:43:59,011 --> 00:44:03,891
And as luck would have it,
Ica had the jackets and joggers.

834
00:44:03,974 --> 00:44:05,392
So she said, "Okay, just use them"

835
00:44:05,476 --> 00:44:08,604
It's as if the whole Team BINI
went all out.

836
00:44:08,687 --> 00:44:09,688
Go all out.

837
00:44:09,772 --> 00:44:13,025
It's our way of saying that, in life,

838
00:44:13,108 --> 00:44:15,027
there's so much negativity.

839
00:44:15,110 --> 00:44:16,904
Let's keep it light.

840
00:44:16,987 --> 00:44:20,324
Even I found it funny.

841
00:44:20,407 --> 00:44:21,700
Like, okay, it was effective.

842
00:44:21,784 --> 00:44:23,619
[laughs]

843
00:44:23,702 --> 00:44:24,870
It was a success.

844
00:44:24,953 --> 00:44:28,707
And it seems like a lot
of people got triggered again.

845
00:44:28,791 --> 00:44:30,167
There was no hate in that action,

846
00:44:30,250 --> 00:44:32,628
it was more like,
"Okay, we're going to have fun."

847
00:44:32,711 --> 00:44:34,797
That was the first and
last time we're doing that,

848
00:44:34,880 --> 00:44:36,298
because no matter what we do,

849
00:44:36,382 --> 00:44:37,800
no matter what we say,

850
00:44:37,883 --> 00:44:39,218
no matter how much we clapback,

851
00:44:39,301 --> 00:44:41,679
people will always have something to say.

852
00:44:41,762 --> 00:44:44,431
And I bet you are still going to.

853
00:44:44,515 --> 00:44:46,433
But that's okay, I don't care.

854
00:44:46,517 --> 00:44:47,518
I'm happy with it.

855
00:44:47,601 --> 00:44:50,187
I was like, "Director, I'm good now."

856
00:44:50,270 --> 00:44:53,023
"I won't reply or comment anymore.

857
00:44:53,107 --> 00:44:55,526
With everything I see on social media,

858
00:44:55,609 --> 00:44:58,946
I've got to take care of my mental health.

859
00:44:59,029 --> 00:45:00,614
It's just better to be quiet.

860
00:45:00,697 --> 00:45:02,991
I feel like that's where I am at now.

861
00:45:03,075 --> 00:45:05,744
Status update: Quiet mode.

862
00:45:07,704 --> 00:45:10,499
[wind blowing]

863
00:45:15,796 --> 00:45:17,965
[fans screaming]

864
00:45:33,313 --> 00:45:39,987
["Strings" continues]

865
00:45:44,616 --> 00:45:47,161
[screaming]

866
00:45:52,416 --> 00:45:54,460
[music fades]

867
00:45:54,543 --> 00:45:57,796
When we got there, whoa,
there were so many people!

868
00:45:57,880 --> 00:46:00,299
It was like they did it for us.
They came out to see us.

869
00:46:00,382 --> 00:46:02,259
It's such a good feeling.

870
00:46:02,342 --> 00:46:05,429
I love it when the airport is packed.

871
00:46:05,512 --> 00:46:10,017
But it's even better when they
respect our personal space.

872
00:46:10,100 --> 00:46:12,978
That's when I really appreciate them.

873
00:46:13,061 --> 00:46:19,735
- [cheering, screaming]
- [upbeat music playing]

874
00:46:19,818 --> 00:46:22,321
The last time we visited GenSan,

875
00:46:22,404 --> 00:46:24,281
only six Blooms welcomed us.

876
00:46:24,364 --> 00:46:29,119
["Na Na Na" by BINI playing]

877
00:46:29,203 --> 00:46:31,288
[fan] Oh they're approaching us!

878
00:46:31,371 --> 00:46:32,289
[fan screaming]

879
00:46:32,372 --> 00:46:35,834
We were really not expecting
that BINI would approach us.

880
00:46:35,918 --> 00:46:37,503
[fan] Oh my god! Can I get an autograph?

881
00:46:37,586 --> 00:46:39,463
Can I get an autograph?

882
00:46:39,546 --> 00:46:44,384
We were shocked when
Maloi herself came over.

883
00:46:44,468 --> 00:46:47,012
[fan] Sorry, but oh my god,

884
00:46:47,095 --> 00:46:49,389
we're totally fangirling!

885
00:46:49,473 --> 00:46:53,310
I know, and we all know
it's hard to get close to BINI

886
00:46:53,393 --> 00:46:55,187
and interact with them,

887
00:46:55,270 --> 00:46:59,900
but we're still supporting
BINI because they deserve it.

888
00:46:59,983 --> 00:47:03,153
They worked hard for it.

889
00:47:03,237 --> 00:47:04,613
This is our signed tarpaulin of BINI.

890
00:47:04,696 --> 00:47:06,990
So we had the chance to
take pictures with each of them.

891
00:47:07,074 --> 00:47:09,535
Of course, they were just six.

892
00:47:12,079 --> 00:47:18,460
So I'm an OG small town girl from Bicol.

893
00:47:18,544 --> 00:47:22,422
My life before was way too simple.

894
00:47:22,506 --> 00:47:24,091
I rarely made the trip to the mall

895
00:47:24,174 --> 00:47:25,509
because it was so far from where I lived.

896
00:47:25,592 --> 00:47:28,011
It's like in the countryside,
up in the mountains.

897
00:47:28,095 --> 00:47:33,809
[glum music playing]

898
00:47:33,892 --> 00:47:36,520
Back when her father was still alive,

899
00:47:36,603 --> 00:47:38,522
she was probably around three years old,

900
00:47:38,605 --> 00:47:43,610
we had the radio on and
she was humming along with it.

901
00:47:43,694 --> 00:47:50,701
Her father told me, "Listen to this, Lou."

902
00:47:51,285 --> 00:47:53,120
And this here is my Mama.

903
00:47:53,203 --> 00:47:55,205
She's a stay-at-home mother.

904
00:47:55,289 --> 00:47:57,416
[Gwen] <i>I'm the youngest of five kids,</i>

905
00:47:57,499 --> 00:48:00,127
<i>and I'm the only girl in the family.</i>

906
00:48:00,210 --> 00:48:01,712
My mom is a single mom.

907
00:48:01,795 --> 00:48:05,966
My dad's gone, so there's
no one else to work for us.

908
00:48:06,049 --> 00:48:07,718
She really struggled to find a job.

909
00:48:07,801 --> 00:48:09,511
"Mama, let's go to church."

910
00:48:09,595 --> 00:48:14,057
"I'm going to pray to God and
ask him to bring Papa back."

911
00:48:14,141 --> 00:48:17,102
<i>Then she said, "Mama, if you're good,</i>

912
00:48:17,185 --> 00:48:19,438
the Lord grants what you ask for, right?"

913
00:48:19,521 --> 00:48:23,984
It's so hard to explain to her...

914
00:48:25,485 --> 00:48:29,948
How do I tell her that
her father isn't coming back?

915
00:48:31,491 --> 00:48:33,285
It's there?

916
00:48:34,870 --> 00:48:37,122
[Gwen] <i>We just relied on
the pension back then.</i>

917
00:48:37,205 --> 00:48:41,335
There were five of us kids,
and we all went to college.

918
00:48:41,418 --> 00:48:42,586
<i>We had no idea how
we were going to survive.</i>

919
00:48:42,669 --> 00:48:44,254
<i>We were buried in debt.</i>

920
00:48:44,338 --> 00:48:46,673
I didn't expect that at such a young age,

921
00:48:46,757 --> 00:48:49,259
I'd already be able to help my family.

922
00:48:49,343 --> 00:48:51,595
BINI is such a blessing.

923
00:48:51,678 --> 00:48:58,101
[upbeat music playing]

924
00:49:04,274 --> 00:49:06,318
[Maloi] I'm good with anything.

925
00:49:06,401 --> 00:49:08,904
[coach] No, like, is it okay or not?

926
00:49:09,571 --> 00:49:11,698
[Sheena] What about you, Jhoanna?

927
00:49:12,282 --> 00:49:14,117
[coach] It might affect the...

928
00:49:14,201 --> 00:49:15,410
[Jhoanna] Tomorrow is good.

929
00:49:15,494 --> 00:49:16,620
[Sheena] Only Jhoanna can't.

930
00:49:16,703 --> 00:49:18,789
[coach] Also, Maloi and Aiah.

931
00:49:18,872 --> 00:49:20,666
[coach] There.

932
00:49:23,001 --> 00:49:24,294
[coach] Alright, go ahead.

933
00:49:25,379 --> 00:49:29,216
["Na Na Na" by BINI playing]

934
00:49:29,299 --> 00:49:32,010
We had just arrived at the hotel
when I started feeling unwell.

935
00:49:32,094 --> 00:49:34,846
That night, we had a
rehearsal and sound check.

936
00:49:34,930 --> 00:49:38,892
<i>I couldn't even tell what
I was feeling at that point.</i>

937
00:49:38,975 --> 00:49:43,146
My nose was really runny
and I had a high fever.

938
00:49:43,230 --> 00:49:46,400
[Lauren] So what do we do if
Stacey can't make it tonight?

939
00:49:46,483 --> 00:49:47,901
What adjustments are needed?

940
00:49:47,984 --> 00:49:49,820
[coach] Director,
we're just going to wing it.

941
00:49:50,404 --> 00:49:51,321
What are we going to do
about <i>Strings,</i> Coach?

942
00:49:51,405 --> 00:49:52,698
Like, in the roll call portion?

943
00:49:52,781 --> 00:49:54,700
Are the girls just going to wait
for her name to be called?

944
00:49:54,783 --> 00:49:56,868
That's possible, that's possible.

945
00:49:56,952 --> 00:50:00,288
Coach, our concern is
when the whole group's dancing,

946
00:50:00,372 --> 00:50:02,124
and then it's Stacey's part.

947
00:50:02,207 --> 00:50:04,960
We haven't run through all the songs.

948
00:50:05,043 --> 00:50:06,211
Just in case she can't make it,

949
00:50:06,294 --> 00:50:08,714
I'll announce it to the public
before we start

950
00:50:08,797 --> 00:50:09,923
that Stacey can't make it.

951
00:50:10,006 --> 00:50:11,258
I can do the announcement.

952
00:50:11,341 --> 00:50:15,095
If one of us isn't there,
it's so noticeable, like...

953
00:50:15,178 --> 00:50:16,596
<i>the energy is lacking.</i>

954
00:50:16,680 --> 00:50:18,223
<i>Sometimes, for example, we're going out</i>

955
00:50:18,306 --> 00:50:19,599
<i>and, let's say, there
are only seven of us,</i>

956
00:50:19,683 --> 00:50:22,602
we'll be like, "Who's missing?"

957
00:50:22,686 --> 00:50:24,396
Something feels off.

958
00:50:24,479 --> 00:50:26,606
It's very obvious when we're performing.

959
00:50:26,690 --> 00:50:32,320
Wow, the Lord really amazed me
because he gave me a miracle.

960
00:50:32,404 --> 00:50:34,406
And then it was like
something came over me,

961
00:50:34,489 --> 00:50:35,907
and I suddenly felt better.

962
00:50:35,991 --> 00:50:39,202
I told myself that I have to perform.

963
00:50:39,286 --> 00:50:41,747
I can't miss the last BINIverse.

964
00:50:41,830 --> 00:50:46,710
[upbeat music playing]

965
00:50:46,793 --> 00:50:49,755
"OMG! BINI, see you in GenSan!
So nervous. Platinum, let's go!"

966
00:50:49,838 --> 00:50:51,423
"First time back in
the Philippines in three years,

967
00:50:51,506 --> 00:50:52,841
and I'll finally see BINI in GenSan!"

968
00:50:52,924 --> 00:50:54,885
"This Bloom is traveling
10 hours by land in July

969
00:50:54,968 --> 00:50:56,470
just to see you in GenSan."

970
00:50:58,597 --> 00:51:00,265
"First time being a die-hard
fan, and it's for BINI.

971
00:51:00,348 --> 00:51:01,641
I'll make the effort for you, girls.

972
00:51:01,725 --> 00:51:03,226
So proud and excited
to see you in GenSan."

973
00:51:03,310 --> 00:51:09,775
[upbeat music continues]

974
00:51:13,487 --> 00:51:19,910
["Here With You" by BINI playing]

975
00:51:19,993 --> 00:51:24,581
[singing] <i>♪ I saw the line
Of a thousand other dreams ♪</i>

976
00:51:24,664 --> 00:51:25,791
<i>♪ Coming true ♪</i>

977
00:51:25,874 --> 00:51:29,419
<i>♪ Nervous faces and heart races ♪</i>

978
00:51:29,503 --> 00:51:30,587
<i>♪ Can I come through ♪</i>

979
00:51:30,670 --> 00:51:32,297
I don't think we ever were...

980
00:51:33,173 --> 00:51:35,050
...prepared for this.

981
00:51:35,133 --> 00:51:37,219
We never assumed it would happen.

982
00:51:37,302 --> 00:51:39,346
We just hoped it would happen.

983
00:51:39,429 --> 00:51:41,890
[singing]<i>♪ New phases
Now I know where my place is ♪</i>

984
00:51:41,973 --> 00:51:43,225
It wasn't like overnight,

985
00:51:43,308 --> 00:51:47,437
but in a way, it just kind of happened.

986
00:51:47,521 --> 00:51:49,648
Most people don't understand

987
00:51:49,731 --> 00:51:50,899
what we're going through right now.

988
00:51:50,982 --> 00:51:53,693
There are things that
only the eight of us know.

989
00:51:53,777 --> 00:51:55,737
[singing]<i>♪ Now here with you ♪</i>

990
00:51:55,821 --> 00:51:56,988
I often say,

991
00:51:57,072 --> 00:51:58,323
"Lord, I'm exhausted."

992
00:51:58,406 --> 00:52:01,910
But He keeps giving me signs
not to give up.

993
00:52:01,993 --> 00:52:04,830
Because He's not done writing
my story, our story yet.

994
00:52:04,913 --> 00:52:06,456
[singing] <i>♪ Let's paint the sky ♪</i>

995
00:52:06,540 --> 00:52:08,416
He knows I still have a purpose here,

996
00:52:08,500 --> 00:52:10,669
so I won't give up just yet.

997
00:52:10,752 --> 00:52:12,671
<i>♪ Holding on to all that we could be ♪</i>

998
00:52:12,754 --> 00:52:14,506
<i>♪ Gonna makе it right ♪</i>

999
00:52:14,589 --> 00:52:16,258
[Sheena] Angpa and Mommy
are not here anymore.

1000
00:52:16,341 --> 00:52:17,217
When I talk to God,

1001
00:52:17,300 --> 00:52:18,301
I feel like I'm talking to them too,

1002
00:52:18,385 --> 00:52:19,719
because I know they're together.

1003
00:52:19,803 --> 00:52:24,432
They're looking out for me,
talking about me.

1004
00:52:24,516 --> 00:52:27,102
I update them on
what's happening in my life.

1005
00:52:27,185 --> 00:52:29,688
When I was in Gensan,
I was like, "Thank you, Lord."

1006
00:52:29,771 --> 00:52:33,775
What a way to end our BINIverse.

1007
00:52:34,776 --> 00:52:36,820
[singing] <i>♪ Do we like the view ♪</i>

1008
00:52:36,903 --> 00:52:39,906
This year has been crazy busy.

1009
00:52:39,990 --> 00:52:42,617
I'd get home and just pass out.

1010
00:52:42,701 --> 00:52:45,036
Then I'd wake up in the middle
of the night to get ready.

1011
00:52:45,120 --> 00:52:46,705
We kept reminding each other

1012
00:52:46,788 --> 00:52:52,460
that this is what we've been praying for.

1013
00:52:53,086 --> 00:52:55,005
Here comes the emotional part.

1014
00:52:55,088 --> 00:52:56,423
Just kidding. [chuckles]

1015
00:52:56,506 --> 00:52:58,091
But seriously, the saddest part was...

1016
00:52:59,301 --> 00:53:02,554
...coming home to an empty house.

1017
00:53:02,637 --> 00:53:05,682
I was messaging with Mama earlier...

1018
00:53:06,391 --> 00:53:09,227
...and I sent her my goofiest face.

1019
00:53:09,311 --> 00:53:11,688
I asked, "Mom, do you still love
me even if I look like this?"

1020
00:53:11,771 --> 00:53:13,023
[chuckles]

1021
00:53:13,106 --> 00:53:15,984
And she said, "I missed that side of you."

1022
00:53:17,152 --> 00:53:19,321
I'm really, really grateful
for all of the blessings

1023
00:53:19,404 --> 00:53:21,615
that we've been receiving right now.

1024
00:53:21,698 --> 00:53:25,911
But time is really
what we end up sacrificing.

1025
00:53:25,994 --> 00:53:30,540
[singing] <i>♪ We just need to look around ♪</i>

1026
00:53:30,624 --> 00:53:33,793
<i>- ♪ Now here with you ♪
- ♪ Yeah ♪</i>

1027
00:53:33,877 --> 00:53:36,004
<i>- ♪ Found something new ♪
- ♪ Found something new ♪</i>

1028
00:53:36,087 --> 00:53:36,963
<i>♪ Through the dark nights ♪</i>

1029
00:53:37,047 --> 00:53:41,217
<i>♪ The highlights... ♪</i>

1030
00:53:41,301 --> 00:53:43,720
[Aiah] I've learned so much
from the girls,

1031
00:53:43,803 --> 00:53:47,682
especially during that
really tough time for me.

1032
00:53:47,766 --> 00:53:49,601
You could say it was my "anxiety era"

1033
00:53:49,684 --> 00:53:52,187
because I didn't want to talk.

1034
00:53:52,270 --> 00:53:54,105
I was just observing.

1035
00:53:54,189 --> 00:53:56,608
[Aiah] I saw their strength and dedication

1036
00:53:56,691 --> 00:53:59,402
because we've been through
so much together.

1037
00:53:59,486 --> 00:54:02,822
So I really commend the girls for that.

1038
00:54:02,906 --> 00:54:07,827
["Here With You" by BINI playing]

1039
00:54:07,911 --> 00:54:10,580
I feel like last year, I was just...

1040
00:54:12,207 --> 00:54:13,291
I was just a baby.

1041
00:54:13,375 --> 00:54:15,293
Like, still baby Mikha, you know?

1042
00:54:15,877 --> 00:54:17,587
She was on the road there, you know?

1043
00:54:17,671 --> 00:54:19,839
Like, walking those steps, and bam!

1044
00:54:19,923 --> 00:54:21,216
[Mikha] She's here now.

1045
00:54:21,299 --> 00:54:23,093
And I still have a long way to go.

1046
00:54:23,176 --> 00:54:24,886
I still want to do so many things.

1047
00:54:26,721 --> 00:54:28,515
I got to know who Gwen really is,

1048
00:54:28,598 --> 00:54:33,103
especially the things
I have to improve on.

1049
00:54:33,186 --> 00:54:37,107
We have each other's back,
we care for each other.

1050
00:54:37,190 --> 00:54:43,780
["Here With You" by BINI playing]

1051
00:54:46,783 --> 00:54:49,828
[cheering, applauding]

1052
00:54:49,911 --> 00:54:50,912
It really blows us away!

1053
00:54:50,996 --> 00:54:52,414
So amazing.
I didn't think it was possible.

1054
00:54:52,497 --> 00:54:53,873
It felt like we were in the sky,

1055
00:54:53,957 --> 00:54:55,375
and the fans, they were our stars.

1056
00:54:56,042 --> 00:54:58,628
[Jhoanna]
Yes, the sea of lights
has always been our dream.

1057
00:54:58,712 --> 00:55:02,382
Because we experienced
total darkness, right?

1058
00:55:02,465 --> 00:55:05,176
I was amazed.
I teared up, but just a little.

1059
00:55:05,260 --> 00:55:08,221
[Mikha]
I appreciate the Blooms
everywhere we go.

1060
00:55:08,304 --> 00:55:09,556
I feel like they,

1061
00:55:09,639 --> 00:55:11,099
as much as possible,

1062
00:55:11,182 --> 00:55:15,687
want us to feel the support
that they give to us.

1063
00:55:15,770 --> 00:55:21,609
[tense music playing]

1064
00:55:21,693 --> 00:55:23,111
[Jhoanna] I had a vertigo attack.

1065
00:55:23,194 --> 00:55:27,407
My vision got really blurry
from all the cheering.

1066
00:55:27,490 --> 00:55:28,616
I was wearing in-ears

1067
00:55:28,700 --> 00:55:30,702
and the mic was picking up the screams.

1068
00:55:30,785 --> 00:55:32,495
Aside from that, we were on
our feet dancing, performing

1069
00:55:32,579 --> 00:55:34,122
for three whole hours.

1070
00:55:34,205 --> 00:55:36,916
I left during the last part of our concert

1071
00:55:37,000 --> 00:55:39,586
before anything could happen
that everyone would see.

1072
00:55:39,669 --> 00:55:41,337
So, I just stepped out.

1073
00:55:41,421 --> 00:55:44,049
At that time,
the exhaustion really piled up.

1074
00:55:44,132 --> 00:55:47,218
She suddenly left, and I realized...

1075
00:55:47,302 --> 00:55:52,724
she was gone because
she was feeling really bad.

1076
00:55:52,807 --> 00:55:56,895
[Maloi] I have a soft spot for Jhoanna.

1077
00:55:56,978 --> 00:56:01,399
They all are, but since
she's one of the youngest,

1078
00:56:01,483 --> 00:56:04,486
she's definitely one of my soft spots.

1079
00:56:08,698 --> 00:56:13,578
Honestly, I wasn't surprised
she left at that time.

1080
00:56:13,661 --> 00:56:19,626
I think it's because
of the heat and her cold,

1081
00:56:19,709 --> 00:56:22,462
plus the pressure.
It was just a mix of feelings.

1082
00:56:22,545 --> 00:56:24,005
You know, Jho, she's the leader.

1083
00:56:24,089 --> 00:56:26,007
She usually assigns the spiels.

1084
00:56:26,591 --> 00:56:30,011
She handles all the planning
and last-minute changes.

1085
00:56:30,095 --> 00:56:31,012
So she has a lot on her mind.

1086
00:56:31,096 --> 00:56:32,806
Plus she's exhausted.

1087
00:56:32,889 --> 00:56:34,599
So her body just gave out.

1088
00:56:34,682 --> 00:56:36,142
I just couldn't go on.

1089
00:56:36,226 --> 00:56:38,353
I didn't have the strength.

1090
00:56:38,436 --> 00:56:41,564
And I was only concerned about my head.

1091
00:56:41,648 --> 00:56:44,609
It was like pure chaos inside my head.

1092
00:56:44,692 --> 00:56:48,988
It was definitely vertigo.

1093
00:56:49,072 --> 00:56:56,079
[unsettling music playing]

1094
00:57:04,129 --> 00:57:06,381
- [producer] Get well soon.
- [Jhoanna] I'm okay now.

1095
00:57:07,590 --> 00:57:09,717
[Jhoanna] No need, I'm good.

1096
00:57:09,801 --> 00:57:11,177
[producer] Your mother is asking.

1097
00:57:11,261 --> 00:57:13,388
I think she knew something happened to you

1098
00:57:13,471 --> 00:57:16,391
since you suddenly
disappeared from the stage.

1099
00:57:16,474 --> 00:57:18,476
[producer] Hi, Miss Jhonna.

1100
00:57:18,560 --> 00:57:22,814
Jhoanna collapsed after the concert.

1101
00:57:22,897 --> 00:57:27,110
She got to leave the stage
and she's okay now.

1102
00:57:27,193 --> 00:57:29,612
She was assisted by the doctor and nurse.

1103
00:57:30,155 --> 00:57:31,531
She was dizzy.

1104
00:57:31,614 --> 00:57:38,496
Jhoanna that time wasn't
really feeling well that time.

1105
00:57:38,580 --> 00:57:40,790
She's safe, she just needs to rest.

1106
00:57:40,874 --> 00:57:46,087
[unsettling music continues]

1107
00:57:50,592 --> 00:57:52,552
[Colet] I don't really share
this with the girls,

1108
00:57:52,635 --> 00:57:55,013
but their presence is just--

1109
00:57:55,096 --> 00:57:58,892
I mean, my family's not here,
but at least I have them.

1110
00:57:58,975 --> 00:58:01,853
They've become my family here.

1111
00:58:01,936 --> 00:58:07,901
["Na Na Nandito Lang" by BINI playing]

1112
00:58:07,984 --> 00:58:13,198
When I'm at home,
I feel how exhausted I am.

1113
00:58:13,281 --> 00:58:17,368
But when I'm at shoots,
I'm just happy and enjoy myself.

1114
00:58:17,452 --> 00:58:19,078
I think it's because of the girls.

1115
00:58:19,162 --> 00:58:22,916
["Na Na Nandito Lang" by BINI continues]

1116
00:58:22,999 --> 00:58:29,881
They love me in a way
that no one else ever has.

1117
00:58:29,964 --> 00:58:33,593
[Maloi] I don't even second-guess myself

1118
00:58:33,676 --> 00:58:36,387
or worry about what they think,

1119
00:58:36,471 --> 00:58:40,600
because I know they love me.

1120
00:58:41,559 --> 00:58:44,145
I've realized that the girls are the ones

1121
00:58:44,229 --> 00:58:46,981
who really help me
become a stronger person.

1122
00:58:47,065 --> 00:58:49,025
They're the only ones who will
tell me the truth straight up.

1123
00:58:49,108 --> 00:58:51,027
We always have each other's backs,

1124
00:58:51,110 --> 00:58:52,862
no matter what.

1125
00:58:52,946 --> 00:58:56,449
["Na Na Nandito Lang" by BINI continues]

1126
00:58:56,533 --> 00:58:57,617
It's hard to put into words

1127
00:58:57,700 --> 00:58:58,785
when it has anything to do with the girls.

1128
00:58:58,868 --> 00:59:00,995
We're all in the same boat.

1129
00:59:01,788 --> 00:59:04,415
We're all going, like,
same pace, you know.

1130
00:59:04,499 --> 00:59:07,126
[Mikha] And we're all going
through this together.

1131
00:59:07,669 --> 00:59:13,383
["Na Na Nandito Lang" by BINI continues]

1132
00:59:13,466 --> 00:59:17,387
I think every year,
our bond is getting stronger.

1133
00:59:17,470 --> 00:59:21,641
Because every year we get to be together

1134
00:59:21,724 --> 00:59:24,185
is another challenge, another experience.

1135
00:59:24,269 --> 00:59:26,521
[Aiah] Every year, it gets tougher.

1136
00:59:26,604 --> 00:59:30,650
Because it is in tough times
that you get to be strong.

1137
00:59:30,733 --> 00:59:33,695
["Na Na Nandito Lang" by BINI continues]

1138
00:59:33,778 --> 00:59:37,782
[Sheena] I trust and believe
we're still going to go bigger.

1139
00:59:37,865 --> 00:59:40,785
You know, the ultimate goal
is really global domination.

1140
00:59:40,868 --> 00:59:42,787
And we're going to prepare ourselves.

1141
00:59:42,870 --> 00:59:47,834
At least now, we know how it is
and we can prepare for it.

1142
00:59:48,960 --> 00:59:52,505
[Gwen] That's always been
the goal, global domination.

1143
00:59:52,589 --> 00:59:53,506
That's really it.

1144
00:59:53,590 --> 00:59:55,508
That's what we've been
holding onto since we started.

1145
00:59:55,592 --> 00:59:57,385
So we will continue,

1146
00:59:57,468 --> 01:00:01,139
and we won't stop until
we've reached that.

1147
01:00:01,222 --> 01:00:07,895
["Na Na Nandito Lang" by BINI continues]

1148
01:00:15,945 --> 01:00:22,577
["Na Na Nandito Lang" by BINI playing]
